The cut marks the first time policymakers have changed the rate since a 100 basis points hike in October last year. 

Emmanuel Tumusiime-Mutebile, the bank’s Governor, said a benign outlook for inflation had also provided room for easing. “Economic activity seems to have slackened in the first half of 2019 compared to the second half of 2018,” Tumusiime-Mutebile said. The bank targets a medium-term core inflation rate of 5%. --Reuters--